    <exercise xmlns:q="http://cnx.rice.edu/qml/1.0" id="fs-id2595222" type="problem-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1663574">    <para id="import-auto-id2507424"><emphasis>Unreasonable Results</emphasis></para><para id="eip-id1945027">(a) Find the value of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>γ</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{γ} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> for the following situation. An astronaut measures the length of her spaceship to be 25.0 m, while an Earth-bound observer measures it to be 100 m. (b) What is unreasonable about this result? (c) Which assumptions are unreasonable or inconsistent?</para>
    </problem>
<solution id="fs-id2635324">
    <para id="import-auto-id1964569">(a) 0.250</para>
    <para id="import-auto-id1296098">(b) <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>γ</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{γ} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> must be ≥1</para>
    <para id="import-auto-id2687718">(c) The Earth-bound observer must measure a shorter length, so it is unreasonable to assume a longer length.</para>
    </solution>
    </exercise><exercise xmlns:q="http://cnx.rice.edu/qml/1.0" id="fs-id1359494" type="problem-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1032174">    <para id="import-auto-id1565866"><emphasis>Unreasonable Results</emphasis></para> <para id="eip-id1765555">A spaceship is heading directly toward the Earth at a velocity of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>800</m:mtext><m:mi>c</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{0 "." "800"c} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>. The astronaut on board claims that he can send a canister toward the Earth at <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>20</m:mtext><m:mi>c</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{1 "." "20"c} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> relative to the Earth. (a) Calculate the velocity the canister must have relative to the spaceship. (b) What is unreasonable about this result? (c) Which assumptions are unreasonable or inconsistent?</para>
    </problem></exercise></section>
